message: "If you use this software or refer to the research it accompanies, please cite both the software (this file) and the paper (see Zenodo DOI when published)."
title: "Continuants: Toward a Theory of Behavioural Persistence in Long-Running LLM Agents"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Krishnan"
    given-names: "Prakash"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0007-5481-6178"
    affiliation: "Independent Researcher"
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/prakash-krishnan/continuants"
url: "https://osf.io/vse2f/"
keywords:
  - LLM agents
  - behavioural drift
  - agent continuity
  - autonomous AI
  - pre-registration
  - replication
abstract: >-
  Continuants is a research project investigating whether long-running
  autonomous LLM agents accumulate behavioural state beyond what context
  replication captures. The work introduces the concept of agents as
  continuants (entities that persist through change) and addresses four
  open questions: distinguishing useful drift from harmful drift,
  extracting useful learnings across an agent fleet, designing shadow
  agents for continuity and review, and deciding when a drifted agent
  should be promoted. This repository holds the experimental code and
  data; the working paper is deposited on Zenodo with a DOI.
